117 * Ego/Vanity Think of a vast ocean filled with water on all sides. A
jar is immersed in it. There is water both inside and outside the jar; but
the water does not become one unless the jar is broken. ...What is the jar?
It is I-consciousnessâ€”the ego. When the I disappears, what is, remains.
